-- equality fast path: returns the user and reads only the matched row
alice
1
-- equality fast path: a non-existent user returns nothing and reads no rows
0
-- IN fast path: returns both users and reads only the matched rows
alice
bob
2
-- equality fast path: a NULL constant matches no rows and raises no exception
0
-- IN fast path: a NULL element is skipped, non-NULL names still match
alice
-- AND fast path: contradictory equalities intersect to the empty set
0
-- AND fast path: equality intersected with IN narrows the candidates
alice
1
-- AND fast path: equality combined with an unrelated condition still narrows by name
alice
1
-- fallback: a constant alias named 'name' must not be mistaken for the column
1
-- fallback: LIKE predicate still returns the right users
alice
bob
carol
-- fallback: a large IN set (above the fast-path limit) falls back to the full scan but stays correct
alice
-- fallback: a duplicate-heavy IN (few distinct values, long list above the limit) falls back to the full scan and stays correct
alice
fell back to full scan
-- fallback: a mostly-NULL IN (long NULL list above the limit) falls back to the full scan and stays correct
alice
-- fallback: counting all users still works
1
